T. kyrghyzica
is very similar to
T. ghissarica
in its wing pattern, differing by its dark brown coloration (paler in
T. ghissarica
), abdominal tergites entirely brown (tergites 1–3 usually largely yellow in
T. ghissarica
), oviscape dark, reddish brown (yellow to orange-yellow in
T. gissarica
), and oviscape and aculeus conspicuously longer than 1.4 mm , and 1.2 of costal cell length (shorter than 1.3 mm , and at most as long as costal cell length in
T. ghissarica
); in addition, aculeus of
T. kyrghyzica
is gradually pointed (
Fig. 27a – b
), whereas in
T. ghissarica
it is strongly pointed to apex (
Fig. 15a – b
).
